racingFormOutcome.overview: Second in three of his four bumpers last season but ran out on hurdle debut in October and both subsequent efforts have been underwhelming; in good hands, though, and may yet get his act together in this sphere.
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E10,000 3yo; fifth foal; dam unraced half-sister to 2m5f-2m6f hurdle winner Mini Moo Min (dam of smart chaser Annacotty) and 3m and 3m7f cross-country chase winner Wonderkid out of 2m3f-3m1f hurdle/chase winning sister to smart staying chaser Bigsun

racingFormOutcome.overview: With a top stable but was well-beaten 50-1 shot on debut at Warwick (2m, good to soft) last month and could be considered only if much stronger in the betting here.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class 10-12f colt, top-class jumps sire; sire of Cooldine, Benefficient & Monksland
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E75,000 3yo; 4th foal; half-brother to 2m hurdle winner Lord Charisma; dam French 1m7f 3yo hurdle winner, sister to 2m-2m4f hurdle/chase winner Lord Dal, 2m3f-3m hurdle/chase winner Lord Youky and to dam of high-class jumpers Geos and Kapgarde

racingFormOutcome.overview: Won an Irish point in June and made quite pleasing rules debut when second in good-ground Hexham bumper in October; made disappointing start to hurdling career when beaten about 75l at Southwell (3m) last month but still has an each-way shout here.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class, multiple-winning jumper in France, formerly in France, sire of Madison du Berlais
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 25,000 Asc July 16; seventh foal; brother to 2m/2m7f hurdle winner TB Broke Her, half-brother to 2m7f hurdle winner Keltic Crisis; dam useful 2m4f-3m hurdle winner, also won 1m4f/1m5f on Flat, half-sister to useful Flat stayer/hurdler Satin Lover.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Displayed at least some promise in all three bumpers but finished well down the field when 50-1 for hurdle debut at Uttoxeter (2m, good to soft) last month.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 10-12f winner at 3-5, 1/2 to Dream Well; sires high-class jumpers inc Rule The World
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 4th foal; half-sister to winners Actinpieces (useful 2m-3m hurdle/chase), Bonnet's Vino (2m3f-2m4f hurdle) and Bouggietopieces (2m4f chase/2m5f hurdle); dam placed 2m-2m4f hurdles/chase, sister to 2m4f hurdle winner Harley

racingFormOutcome.overview: Failed to build on reasonably encouraging bumper debut when soundly beaten at Fakenham six weeks ago; makes hurdle debut today.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: winning 2yo, top-class miler at 3, won Sussex Stakes; dual-purpose sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First foal; dam triple point winner, sister to 2m5f-3m1f chase winner Mr Splodge and point winner Lord Of The Ride out of 2m4f hurdle winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Won a maiden point in May 2015, his fourth start, and made quite promising stable debut when fifth of eight in Ascot bumper in October of that year; switches to hurdles after 403-day absence but market support will bring him into the equation.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class stayer, brother to Opera House, leading British jumps sire inc Special Tiara/Thistlecrack
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First foal; dam placed 2m4f hurdle, half-sister to 2m1f hurdle winner Cabinet Minster out of maiden sister to high-class bumper/2m-2m5f hurdle winner Monsignor

racingFormOutcome.overview: Made low-key debut when midfield in Worcester bumper in October; pedigree suggests today's longer trip will suit but significant improvement required.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class 2yo then top class over 8-12f, can get useful 2yos, better record with 3yo+
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E12,000 4yo; first foal dam unraced half-sister to useful 2m6f/3m chase winner Carrigeen Lechuga, out of 2m3f-2m5f chase winning half-sister to useful chaser Carrigeen Kerria (stayed 3m1f)

racingFormOutcome.owner: Galloping On The South Downs Partnership
racingFormOutcome.overview: Finally delivered on promise shown in novice company in 2014 when winning Huntingdon handicap (3m1f, good) by 24l under very positive ride in October; can cope with today's drop back in trip and play a leading role.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: dual Derby winner, can get high-class runners, most with stamina, dual-purpose sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E1,000 Y, 19,000 3yo; fifth foal; dam unraced half-sister to bumper winner Blayney James out of 7f 2yo winning sister to 1m2f Flat/smart 2m juvenile hurdle winner Crowded House

racingFormOutcome.overview: Ran well for a long way when third on handicap hurdle debut at Southwell (2m, good) in October but lost his position worryingly quickly over 2m4f at Fakenham later that month; remains lightly raced and could have a future over fences but comes with risks attached; sports first-time hood.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: smart French hurdler, half-brother to Robin Des Pres, top-class jumps sire inc Quevega
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E58,000 3yo; first foal; dam placed 2m/2m2f hurdles, half-sister to 2m-2m4f hurdle/useful chase winner Sobers and to the dam of useful 2m jumper Turn Over Sivola out of useful French juvenile hurdle winner

racingFormEvent.title: Actuate Marketing Maiden Open National Hunt Flat Race (5) 4-6yo
racingFormEvent.overview: Nicky Henderson's filly Crystal Gazing might well be capable of better than she showed when third in a run-of-the-mill event at Southwell last month, while Josie Abbing displayed promise on her second start and can improve. However, NOEL'S BOY put in a good front-running shift before succumbing to the odds-on favourite over C&D on his rules debut 24 days ago and can go one better today.[Chris Wilson]

racingFormOutcome.overview: 0-10 when trained in France and was soundly beaten on first two British starts, but took big step in right direction when third over hurdles in first-time visor here (2m, good) on Thursday and runs off a 4lb lower chase mark today; refitted cheekpieces the headgear of choice this time.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class French jumper, useful jumps sire; progeny inc Garde La Victoire and Milord Thomas
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Fourth foal; half-brother to French 2m5f chase winner Asti Du Domaine; dam fourth 1m4f AQPS Flat from three starts, half-sister to 1m5f and 1n6f AQPS Flat/2m1f-2m3f chase winner Hadol De Neulliac, granddaughter of 1m1f-1m4f AQPS Flat winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Kept on for respectable third at Cartmel (2m5f, good) on penultimate appearance but was pulled up when last in action and is now 0-48 over fences; makes very little appeal from 10lb out of the weights.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class 3yo stayer, sired Flat winners, top-class NH sire, sire of Moscow Flyer. Died 2007
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E2,500 F, E2,800 Y; second foal; dam well held 5.5f-1m, half-sister to six winners inc Tender Process (5f-7f, inc AW), Dorn Dancer (5f-6f) and Lady Pahia (7f) out of fairly useful 6f-7f winner.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Three chase wins since joining Anthony Honeyball this summer, the latest in small-field event at Market Rasen (2m1f, good) last month; looked very one-paced when second to Next Exit here (2m4f, firm) recently but there's a good chance she'll be in the mix again.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: smart 10-12f performer, also high-class hurdler, by Night Shift, high-class jumps sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Seventh foal; half-sister to 5f/6f AW (inc Fibresand) winner Stargem, 1m2f AW winner Foxtrot Charlie and Spanish 1m winner Smoking Bluff; dam 1m-1m2f winner (inc Fibresand), out of 1m2f/1m4f winning half-sister to leading Hong Kong performer River Verdon

racingFormOutcome.overview: Lightly raced 10yo who was close second in small-field event over C&D (heavy) on chase debut in February; pulled up at Lingfield the following month, though, and is back from another break today.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class runner with abundant stamina, dual-purpose sire, gets useful performers under both codes
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 6,000gns Y; ninth foal; half-brother to Italian 7f winner Rudy Spice, French 1m4f and 1m5f Flat/2n2f hurdle winner Luarca and Korean 7f winner Be My Day; dam maiden half-sister to Gold Cup winner Celeric and 1m4f Gr 2 winner Sesame.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Gained first win since August 2012 when fending off Unify from 20lb out of the handicap here (2m4f, firm) ten days ago; effectively only 2lb higher under a penalty today but is not one for a huge amount of faith.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class miler, dual-purpose sire, capable of getting smart 2yos from summer onwards
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 1,000 Don Aug 2013; second foal; dam modest Irish 1m4f and 1m6f Flat winner, half-sister to modest 1m/9f Fibresand/2m1f hurdle winner Elheba

racingFormOutcome.overview: Ran well to a point when fifth in recent Lingfield handicap (2m3f, soft) and will find this race easier but has very patchy record over hurdles and is nothing like the force of old; tongue-tie/cheekpieces refitted.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: tough, smart prolific 5-6f winner at 2-6, from fast family; fair start with first 2yos
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 26,000 Y; third foal; half-brother to 5f winner Sonko (inc at 2/mainly AW inc Fibresand, RPR 87); dam 7f/1m winner (83), half-sister to prolific sprint winner (inc on AW) Gone'N'Dunnett and 6f 2yo winner Deeday Bay, out of half-sister to Mill Reef winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Made all to win Worcester maiden (2m, good) in first-time cheekpieces in July and finished second in a handicap over that C&D soon afterwards; good chance on that evidence but hasn't been in same form in recent months and was flattered by his proximity when second in Stratford seller (2m2f, good; first-time visor) when last in action; cheekpieces back on today.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: tough and consistent St Leger winner, later won Doncaster Cup, from good family; NH sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E4,400 F; eighth foal; dam unraced sister to high-class staying chaser The Grey Monk, family of Grey Abbey.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Weakened quickly before finishing last of ten in Class 3 handicap at Lingfield last week but is sure to appreciate today's drop in class and will probably be better suited by the faster ground; swaps cheekpieces for first-time visor.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 12f colt, top pedigree; brilliant sire of 2yos, plus progeny progress well, multiple champ
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 13,000 Ascot Feb 2016; 6th foal; brother to Qatar 1m winner First Sea Lord, half-brother to smart 6f/7f winner Ugo Fire & 7f/1m4f winner Houston Dynimo; dam unraced half-sister to winners, including the dam of Group winners Cabaret & Drumfire

racingFormOutcome.overview: Gave very good account when third to Trapper Peak in C&D seller ten days ago and is better off at the weights with that rival today, but was probably flattered by the way that slowly run event panned out and career strike-rate now stands at 0-30.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: from family of Deep Impact; dual purpose; sire of top-class hurdler Our Conor
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E14,000 Y; fourth foal; half-sister to 6f winner Intibaah (inc at 2/AW; RPR 114) and 5f/6f Italian (inc at 2) winner Maschio Angioino; dam maiden best efforts 7f/1m AW (58), out of Group-placed 1m2f winning half-sister to Almutawakel

racingFormOutcome.overview: Won a handicap chase in April and has bagged two selling hurdles this autumn, the more recent over C&D (good to soft) ten days ago; has a lot less to prove than some of these and ought to make his presence felt again.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top stayer, also r-up in Arc; has sired summer 2yo winners but progeny better with time
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 11,000 Y; 3rd foal; half-brother to bumper/2m hurdle winner Knocklong; dam tough but modest 1m4f-1m6f Flat/2m3f selling hurdle winner, half-sister to 1m1f-1m4f Flat/very useful 2m-2m5f hurdle winner L'Opera, family of Breeders' Cup Turf winner Kotashaan

racingFormOutcome.overview: Claimed for 8,000GBP after winning at Huntingdon (2m, good) for John Flint in October; big player if in similar form here but finished last of nine when making stable debut on the Flat last month and was also disappointing when well-held fourth in 2m4f selling hurdle here on Thursday.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class, tough sprint winner at 2-5, by Shinko Forest; modest start at stud
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 16,000gns F, 30,000 Y, 800 Don Jan 2013; first foal; dam 9.4f winner (RPR 71), closely related to four winners inc Lost In The Moment (smart 1m-1m3f, stays 2m) and Luas Line (6f, at 2, to 1m1f US Grade 1).

racingFormOutcome.overview: Runner-up twice in plating company on the Flat this summer but suffered early mishap in selling handicap hurdle in September and has now been unplaced all seven starts in this sphere; others stronger.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 2yo, then smart sprinter, source of top-class 2yos, progeny also progress well
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Sixth foal; half-brother to winners Shamali (8.6f-1m2f, inc AW Listed; 110), Parhelion (1m4f/1m6f AW; 85), Khazeena (1m AW; 81) and Dear Maurice (6f-1m; 91); dam 1m3f-1m6f (Listed) winner (111), half-sister to 7f Gr 2 winner Nayyir & Leger second Highest.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Placed in Market Rasen handicap (2m2f, good) in August but didn't find much for pressure when well-held third in 2m4f seller here on Thursday; might be suited by today's drop back in trip but others make more appeal.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class 11-14f winner at 3-6 in Germany, also winner of G1 Singapore Int'l Cup; dual purpose sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E11,000 3yo; fourth foal; dam maiden French chaser and half-sister to numerous maidens Flat/jumps, out of sister  smart French jumpers Moncourt and Mon Courtoise

racingFormOutcome.overview: Soundly beaten in both bumpers and was a 50-1 shot when brought down at first flight in C&D seller won by Trapper Peak on recent hurdle debut.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: smart stayer by Green Dancer, dual-purpose sire, few Flat runners
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First foal; dam modest 2m3f/2m5f hurdle winner, out of 7f/1m winning granddaughter of US 8.5f Grade 1 winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Capitalised on sliding handicap mark when winning low-grade event at Plumpton (2m3f, good; first-time blinkers) in October but his revival hasn't gained any momentum and he looked rather laboured when well-held third here (2m6f, firm) on Thursday.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 12-14f performer, won St Leger; high-class jumps sire, progeny inc Briar Hill
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E12,000 3yo, 31,000 Don May 2014; third foal; dam unraced half-sister to useful 7f winner Maumee (stayed 1m1f) and French 5f 2yo Listed winner Mona Em, out of 1m/9f winner.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Won over hurdles in good style at Southwell (2m, good) in August and had Prince Khurram behind when following up in Sedgefield chase (2m, good) soon afterwards; however, has stamina to prove over today's trip and last couple of runs, though perfectly respectable, suggest he's in the grip of the handicapper now.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 2yo/miler, liked soft going, capable of siring top-class runners, dual-purpose sire
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Sixth foal; half-brother to point winner Ballynalty Storm; dam French 1m-1m1f winner; half-sister to 1m4f Flat/2m hurdle winner Bareme.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Made all in fast-ground novice chase at Perth (2m) in June and has reached the frame on all seven other starts over fences, most recently when third in quite valuable handicap at Musselburgh (2m4f, good) last month; commands respect.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class at 10-12f, half-brother to Nashwan; gets 2yo winners from summer, progeny progress
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 65,000gns Nkt Oct 13; 4th foal; half-brother to 1m AW winner Mawasem (RPR 92) & 7f 2yo winner North East Corner (79); dam 7f 2yo GB winner, later useful 1m winner in N.America, sister to Cheveley Park winner Magical Romance, closely related to Alexandrova

racingFormOutcome.overview: Off since finishing down the field at Cheltenham in April and not yet tested on ground quicker than good to soft, but the style of his come-from-behind success at Newbury (2m4f, soft) in March offers hope he can overcome today's 5lb higher mark at some stage.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: unbeaten G1 winner over 7f at 2, unraced at 3+ due to injury, sire of Trading Leather, Pleascach
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 240,000gns Y; 2nd foal; brother to German 1m/1m3f (Listed) winner Black Arrow (RPR 108); dam 1m1f winner (102), sister to 9.4f AW winner Awaaser & half-sister to 6f/7f 2yo winner Amazing Storm out of half-sister to May Hill/Musidora winner Marillette

racingFormOutcome.overview: Well beaten when upped to 3m for handicap debut at Cheltenham in April but displayed significant promise when placed three consecutive times (2m-2m5f) in novice company beforehand and can be given another chance.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: useful 8f 2yo and top-class 12f 3yo, multiple champion jumps sire, progeny inc Denman
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E52,000 3yo; first foal; dam bumper winner/placed 2m4f-2m5f hurdles, half-sister to 2m-2m4f hurdle/chase winner Sam Adams, bumper/2m-3m2f hurdle/very smart chase winner Snoopy Loopy and bumper/2m5f-3m hurdle/chase winner Royal Snoopy

racingFormOutcome.overview: Disappointed when sent off favourite for Listed handicap chase on seasonal debut in October but won three times over hurdles after joining Dan Skelton last year and has a part to play if back on song here.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: smart 1m-10f performer by Linamix, useful dual-purpose sire in France
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Third foal; half-brother to French 2m1f/2m6f chase winner Tintin De L'Oasis; dam well beaten French AQPS Flat/hurdle/chases, half-sister to 1m2f-1m5f Flat/2m2f-2m5f chase winner Bonheur De L'Oasis

racingFormOutcome.overview: Yet to win in Britain and been off since April but gave good account when fourth in valuable juvenile handicap at Newbury (2m3f, good; first-time cheekpieces) on latest start over hurdles and is 4lb lower now; no cheekpieces today; tongue-tie added.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: minor winner over 1m at 2, out of Shadayid; fair start with first 2 crops
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Seventh foal; brother to 5f (France at 2) to 1m1f (Ire) winner Kentra, dam unplaced 6f-7.5f, sister to a 7f winner in Hong Kong out of French 1m3f winning half-sister to French 1m Group 1 winner Mendez

racingFormOutcome.overview: Absent since well beaten in two small-field novice chases in spring 2015; attractively weighted on some of his old hurdle form and seems versatile regarding ground, but it's hard to gauge how much ability remains.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: smart 10-16f colt, Shirley Heights close relative of Darshaan, jumps sire, has sired jumps winners
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E8,000 F, E25,000 3yo, 23,000 Don Nov 2014; fourth foal; dam 2m1f juvenile selling hurdle winner, half-sister to smart 2m-2m4f hurdle/chase winner Chief's Song out of 1m1f-1m2f winner

racingFormOutcome.overview: Winning pointer (on fast ground) who scored on hurdle debut at Taunton (2m3f, heavy) in January and bounced back from a disappointing effort when close third on soft ground there in March; makes handicap debut after 279-day absence but has some scope for improvement.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: top-class 10f runner, gets high-class 2yos over 6-8f, better record with 3yo+, sire of Opinion Poll
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Fifth foal; dam fourth in bumper/2m and 2m5f hurdles from five starts, half-sister to bumper/useful 2m-2m4f hurdle/chase winner Well Ridden out of sister to very useful 2m-3m jumper Ryde Again and to the dam of high-class chaser Teeton Mill

racingFormOutcome.overview: May not be entirely straightforward but is lightly raced for his age and was raised only 2lb for winning 16-runner handicap at Cheltenham (2m5f, good) in October 2015; appeared stretched by 3m1f when third at Warwick on latest outing in May and today's drop back in trip looks the right move.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class, lightly raced miler, sire of German Oaks winner Rosenreihe in first crop
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E2,200 F, E20,000 4yo; first foal; dam unraced sister to bumper/smart 2m hurdle winner Staying Article is granddaughter of Triumph Hurdle winner Shawiya (also 1m4f Flat/2m4f chase winner)

racingFormOutcome.overview: Looked out of sorts on all three hurdle starts this year and finished well down the field in valuable AW handicap when last seen in June; been given a chance by the handicapper but has quite a bit to prove.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: won Arc and Juddmonte International, sire of both stayers and July Cup winner Sakhee's Secret
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: Seventh foal; half-brother to 2m Fibresand bumper winner There And Then; dam useful 1m2f soft-ground handicapper, half-sister to useful performer up to 1m6f /2m hurdle winner Gold Ring, family of smart hurdlers Accipiter and Brave Tornado.

racingFormOutcome.overview: Improved upon disappointing stable debut when winning small-field event from the front at Chepstow (2m7f, good) last month but was quickly back in the doldrums when pulled up at Ludlow on latest outing, and it's hard to know what to expect from him today.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: dual champion, won BC Classic, from good Argentine family; fair source of winners
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: 8th foal; half-brother to 5f-1m1f Flat/2m4f and 2m6f hurdle winner Bolton Hall, 7f 2yo AW winner Cleodora and 7f/8/6f AW winner Foreign Investment; dam twice-raced sister to 1m German Listed winner, out of half-sister to top-class 2yo Folk Art

racingFormOutcome.overview: Not as good as he once was but can be excused last month's defeat over 3m on soft ground and was in decent form on a sound surface beforehand, most notably when winning at Warwick (2m4f, good) in September.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: useful 8f 2yo and top-class 12f 3yo, multiple champion jumps sire, progeny inc Denman
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: E130,000 3yo; 4th foal; half-brother to high-class 2m-2m4f hurdle/chase winner Captain Chris & 2m3f hurdle winner Dream Function; dam won up to 3m over fences but best (high-class) at 2m, half-sister to useful hurdle/chase winner up to 2m3f One More Dream

racingFormOutcome.overview: Ran well when second at Southwell (2m4f, good) on first start for Oliver Sherwood in September and was in front before unseating rider over 3m at Market Rasen last month; soundly beaten at Newbury on recent debut for another new trainer but in much calmer waters here.
racingFormOutcome.sireOverview: high-class autumn 2yo, later top class over 12f, dual-purpose sire, can sire smart 2yos over 7f+
racingFormOutcome.breedingOverview: First foal; dam bumper winner, out of half-sister to 3m-3m2f chase winner Flippance and 3m chase winner Darren The Brave
